SHAZAM-CUSTOM-CATALOG-DISPLAY(1) General Commands Manual SHAZAM-CUSTOM-CATALOG-DISPLAY(1)

NAME

shazam custom-catalog display — Display contents of a custom catalog file

SYNOPSIS

shazam custom-catalog display [--input input] [--properties properties]

DESCRIPTION

Use this command to display the contents of an existing custom catalog file. Each signature and media items entry is displayed to offer information about the contents of a custom catalog file. See shazam-custom-catalog-create(1) for information on how to create a custom catalog file.

OPTIONS

-i,--input input
Path to an existing custom catalog file to be displayed.

-p,--properties properties
A comma separated list of media item properties to display.

SEE ALSO

shazam-custom-catalog-create(1), shazam-custom-catalog-export(1), shazam-custom-catalog-remove(1)
